#0 - Have the instructions of how to play the game satated at the beginning of the game. 
   - As a JAdventure player, I want to know the commands that are used in game. In order to play the game.

   Task 0A. Identifiying how commands are accepted into the interface - points = 5 
   Task 0B. Create a 'help' command that then spits out a list of commands that are needed to play the game. - points = 1
   Task 0C. Integrate this command into the beginning of the game so that a new player knows how to access it. - points = 2

#1 - generic npcs should respawn after x amount of time. 
   - As a JAdventure player, I want to have enemies spawn at random times. So that I can fight them.

   Task 1A. Understand how to create an enemy in the game world - points = 13
   Task 1B. Spawn in an enemy - points = 5
   Task 1C. Create a method of spawning enemies at a certain time. - points = 8
   Task 1D. Create a method of spawning enemies at random times - points = 5

#2 - flesh out teleporting for debugging purposes
   - As a JAdventure developer, I want to be able to telepot anywhere in the world. So that I can debug world issues.

   Task 2A. Understand how a player moves throughout the world. - points = 13
   Task 2B. have a way for a player to teleport short distances in game - points = 8
   Task 2C. Attempt to move the player larger distances - points = 8

